cs.DL, cs.IR, cs.CY, cs.CR, cs.SI 

The paper discusses academic data sharing and its impact on scientific progress, which is relevant to several sub-categories in computer science. The most relevant sub-category is likely cs.DL (Digital Libraries), as the paper focuses on the sharing and publication of research data. The paper also touches on information retrieval (cs.IR) and cybersecurity (cs.CY) in discussing the benefits and risks of data sharing. Additionally, the paper discusses the need for formal recognition of data sharing, which could fall under the sub-categories of cryptography (cs.CR) or social and information networks (cs.SI).
